Detail.BaseText:
Treat yourself to a cool beer after a long day on the slopes. Meet up with friends in the company of good music. Spend a few relaxing hours over a glass of wine or a cocktail after an intense day of skiing. If you are at our Aprés-Ski Tenne – the most popular historical meeting place of the Plan de Corones ski area – you are in the right place.

Every day at the Aprés-Ski Tenne at Plan de Corones, with its warm wooden decor, friendly staff and cordial atmosphere, our DJ Reinhold sets the right mood with good music and fun for our guests. A mug of good, sweet, hot tea or mulled wine is the best way of topping off a lovely evening after an eventful day of skiing. A brandy or a Williams-pear grappa can liven up the evening too. But at the longest bar counter in South Tyrol you can order lots more: beer, wine, fruit juices and whatever else you can wish for. Come and spend some carefree time in the company of nice people.

Detail.BaseText:
You will find our farm restaurant in the centre of the village. We converted part of the old stable into a restaurant in 1997.
Our restaurant features cosy little snugs, where we serve our guests local Tyrolean specialities including Knödel dumplings, Schlutzkrapfen (pasta parcels), Gerstesuppe (a hearty local soup), platters with farm produce and much more. Every Friday we offer roast pork knuckle with various side dishes. Every Saturday we prepare a typical speciality from the Val Pusteria – "Tirschtlan". Tirschtlan are deep-fried pastries and come with three different fillings: potatoes and curds, spinach and curds or sauerkraut. Tirschtlan are usually eaten with Gerstesuppe, a hearty local soup made with barley. In autumn, you can enjoy the local harvest festival feasts known as Törggelen, where a Tyrolean Schlachtplatte (a hearty meal of pork, sausages and sauerkraut) is served. For desert there are chestnuts, other types of nuts, fruit and doughnuts. Come and visit us!

Our costumer usually reach us by sky, and their baggages are transported to destination from our  snowmobiles.
Our shelter is the ideal place for lovers of skiing and quiet of mountains and offers unforgettable landscapes and sunsets.
It's the ideal place to stop and have a break for skiers who need refresh.
Our kitchen offers delicious typical local dishes in addition to many other of italian and mountain cuisine.
Our shelter is the ideal place for families who are looking for peace away from the chaos of the city, but also for those people who love having fun with friends and pass fine days together,  without the annoying thoughts of daily life.

At lunch time we serve you in our restaurant  “Tesselberger Stuben" a variety of international dishes or you can satisfy the hunger in the afternoon with a hearty snack, with different cakes and ice creams. As part of the half board in the evening you can choose between a 3-4 course menu of international dishes, as well as a fresh salad and appetizer buffet. Detail.BaseText:
The court Obermair
Ehrenburg in Kiens,
The first written mention of Obermair goes back to 1318 and is thus one of the oldest farms in the area.
Initially belonged to the court of the Count Goertz, then the estate was frequently sold, inherited and sold again.
Since 1860, guests at the inn run Obermair and already in 1900 the Obermairhof of Falkensteiner family has farmed.
As you can see our kitchen pot is filled to the brim ...
combined, refined dishes with an occasional touch of the exotic. Just the "magic of the diversity of South Tyrol".

Detail.BaseText:
Charming restaurant surrounded by the natural beauty of the “Pustertaler Sonnenstraße”:
Stylish ambience, South Tyrolean farmhouse parlors, large veranda in Tyrolean century style, piano bar with fireplace, idyllic terrace and rustic wine cellar with river stones and old wood with over 500 fine wines. Chef Karl Baumgartner cooks, depending on the seasonal market supply, creative regional dishes but also an italian-mediterranean cuisine. The service of Siegfried and Mary is professional and yet familiar. The experienced team places great emphasis on a personal and warm relationship with the guests, a devise by which the Baumgartner family works for over 25 years. 

Awards: 1 Michelin Star, 2 awards 16 points Gault & Millau, well rated in "Guida del Gambero Rosso", "Guida de l'espresso" and many other restaurant guides!

Detail.BaseText:
Old-Fashioned Hospitality at our Inn

If you like nostalgia, you'll love our traditional inn, the Gasthof Gatterer (Gatterer Inn.) This inn has a long, rich tradition spanning numerous generations of innkeepers, and offers good, wholesome food and cozy lodgings. It is still a popular meeting place in the heart of our village.

Hospitality Just Like in the Good Old Days!

Pull up a chair and relax! The Gasthof Gatterer is proud of its tradition of friendliness and cordiality. And you'll love our hearty dumplings, our bacon treats, or a good glass of wine. Our inn is permeated by a nostalgic atmosphere and the good old styles and traditions of yesteryear. We're looking forward to your visit!
